China Welcomes Indian Foreign Minister 's Speech , FM Spokesman
BEIJING , December 28 ( Xinhua ) -- China has always attached importance to the growth of its good-neighborly , friendly and cooperative ties with India on the basis of the Five Principles of Peaceful Co-existence , Foreign Ministry Spokesman Zhu Bangzao said here today .
Zhu made the remark this afternoon when asked to comment on Indian Foreign Minister Jaswant Singh 's recent speech concerning his dedication to improving India-China relations .
Singh in his speech urged the world 's two most populous nations to improve their bilateral relations .
" We welcome Foreign Minister Singer 's speech , " Zhu said , and the Chinese side hopes that the Indian side will continue to make effective efforts , so as to bring the bilateral relations between the two countries back to the track of normal growth as soon as possible .
" Such a move complies with the fundamental interest of the people of both countries , " Zhu said .
